					Latest Key Developments (Source: Significant Developments)




Millennium pacific group updates on court orders on litigation
Thursday, 29 Sep 2016 08:22am EDT 
Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Ltd <8147.HK> : Reference is made to announcements issued by company dated 14 july 2016 and 27 july 2016 respectively in respect of summons . Court ordered whole proceedings be transferred from companies winding up list to miscellaneous proceedings list . Court ordered, inter alia, that winding up order sought be struck out Source (http://bit.ly/2d9wdWl) Further company coverage: [8147.HK] ((Bangalore.newsroom@thomsonreuters.com;)). 
			
Full Article





Millennium Pacific received writ of summons filed by Lim Hang Young as plaintiff<8147.HK>
Friday, 12 Aug 2016 10:51am EDT 
Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Ltd <8147.HK>: Received a writ of summons filed by lim hang young as the plaintiff . Writ against world link cpa , tang wai ting, samson (an executive director and chairman of the company) . Plaintiff claimed, among other things, that the auditor will fully engaged in auditing and reporting irregularities . Millennium pacific group -plaintiff requested court to grant an order for auditor to restate the 2014 and 2015 audit reports of the company . Plaintiff claimed that tang masterminded and directed the recording of various accounting irregularity and non-compliance practices to the auditor . Plaintiff claimed tang and chan engaged in money laundering practices while dealing in the shares of the company . Millennium pacific group -plaintiff requested the court to grant an order for the auditor to pay compensation to the company for damages . 
			
Full Article





Millennium Pacific Group says received writ of summons filed by Kim, Sungho as plaintiff<8147.HK>
Wednesday, 27 Jul 2016 10:35am EDT 
Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Ltd <8147.HK>: Litigation <8147.HK> . Says received a writ of summons filed by Kim, Sungho as the plaintiff . Company is seeking legal advice in respect of the legal proceeding . Millennium pacific group - plaintiff claimed that dealings in shares of co by CPIT were ultra virus and illegal .Plaintiff requested court to grant an order to rescind the dealings, forfeit relevant shares and rescind any share pledge arrangement. 
			
Full Article





Millennium Pacific Group receives winding up petition filed by Zhi, Charles<8147.HK>
Thursday, 14 Jul 2016 10:05am EDT 
Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Ltd <8147.HK>: Winding up petition against the company . Company received petition filed by Zhi, Charles in court of first instance of high court of Hong Kong . Is currently seeking legal advice in respect of petition with a view to defend winding-up petition against company . Zhi, Charles as petitioner alleged that a unit was injected into co prior to IPO of company based on overstated valuations . Petitioner alleged that certain shareholders of co were engaged in illegal share pledge borrowing . 
			
Full Article





Millennium Pacific Group Holdings issues profit warning<8147.HK>
Tuesday, 12 Jul 2016 07:29am EDT 
Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Ltd <8147.HK>: Profit warning <8147.HK> . Millennium pacific group - expected to continue to record "significant" net loss for the six months ended 30 June 2016 .Expected loss as largest customer of the group has ceased to place order for gps personal navigation devices from the group in June 2015. 
			
